WEBVTT

NOTE Skit begins at anchor #10.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
[caption] THE EPILOGUE, A QUESTION OF BELIEF

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:09.000
[action] Interviewer flanked by a monsignor and an old Don figure.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:20.000
<v Interviewer (John Cleese)>
Good evening, and welcome once again to the Epilogue… instead of discussing God's existence, they have decided to fight for it… determined by two falls, two submissions, or a knockout… Your master of ceremonies—Mr Arthur Waring.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.000
[action] Participants move into a wrestling ring.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:34.000
<v MC (Eric Idle)>
Good evening ladies and gentlemen and welcome… Appearing for Jehovah—the ever popular Monsignor Eddie Gay. [crowd boos] And in the red corner… Dr Tom Jack! [cheers] [caption] Gong.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
[caption] ROUND 1

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:42.000
[action] Real wrestlers throw each other about.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:50.000
<v Interviewer (John Cleese)>
Now Dr Jack's got a flying mare there… full body slam… he's laying it in… standing back… We'll leave the Epilogue for the moment and bring you the result later.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.000
<v Interviewer (John Cleese)>
Oh my God! [action] Pulls out a revolver and shoots off-screen.

